          <h2 class= "darkblue centered">DreamFunded’s Unique Solution to Investor Access:</h2><br>

          <p class= "faq-answer"><strong></strong> </p>

          <p class= "faq-answer">
            DreamFunded has built an exclusive, members only equity crowdfunding platform to address the urgent issues of investor access and founder funding. DreamFunded provides insider access to investors and capital to companies giving them the ability to thrive. We source, screen and organize all investments on our platform in order to present them to our members, who can select and invest in the opportunities that interest them for as little as $1,000. The fees associated with DreamFunded investments are significantly lower than those required by traditional venture funding and angel groups. DreamFunded earns 5% of the total amount invested into each company. This fee is removed from each individual investment at the time it is made. DreamFunded facilitates investments by combining the efficiency of a secure, web-based equity crowdfunding portal with the advantages of specialized software to simplify the investing and fundraising processes.
          </p>

          <br>
          <h2 class= "darkblue centered">CrowdFunding Dilemmas:</h2><br>


          <p class= "faq-answer">
            While crowdfunding promises to offer a new way to raise capital for small companies, a host of challenges hamper existing crowdfunding models:</p>
          <p class= "faq-answer">
            (A) I am not a professional angel investor. How can I minimize some of the high risks associated with early-stage investing? Does DreamFunded perform due diligence?
          </p>

          <p class= "faq-answer paragraph-padding" >
            (a) These are important questions for you to ask before you make any investment. DreamFunded carefully reviews and screens each company, then hand picks each investment that will be featured on our platform. This process takes time but is crucial to help to reduce the chances of investing in an ill-conceived company.  We believe in every company that passes our screening process and makes it onto our platform.
          </p>
          <p class= "faq-answer">
            (B) How do I deal with all the paperwork and investment information for each investment opportunity? Isn't there a lot of research, paperwork, negotiations and time that is required? How can I manage all of this?
          </p>
          <p class= "faq-answer paragraph-padding">
            (b) We pre-negotiate and sign all term sheets, and we administer the deal logistics, paperwork, and future reporting on behalf of our member investors. Investments start as low as $1,000.
          </p>
          <p class= "faq-answer">
            (C) How can an investor who is not part of a VC firm access investments in top-tier companies?
          </p>
          <p class= "faq-answer paragraph-padding">
            (c) DreamFunded has built an extensive network of relationships with some of the largest and most successful VC firms, Angel Groups and Incubators in the world. We leverage these relationships to source and screen top-tier investment opportunities for the DreamFunded platform. Members of DreamFunded have direct access to these investment opportunities, which were previously only available to a select handful of investors.
          </p>

            <p class= "faq-answer">(D) How long will it take for an investment in an early-stage company to pay off?</p>
            <p class= "faq-answer  paragraph-padding">
              (d) The Average time to IPO for a private technology company in Silicon Valley is currently around 11-years. Historically, this long-term investment type has turned off many investors who were looking for more short-term investments but, Title III of the JOBS Act (Regulation CrowdFunding) changed this. Under Title III, shares must be held for a period of 1-year (12-months) unless any of the following conditions are met:
            </p>
            <p class= "faq-answer">
              <ol class= "faq-answer">
                <li class= "faq-answer" style="    font-size: 16px;  line-height: 150%;"> If the issuing company purchases the shares back from the investor.</li>
                <li class= "faq-answer" style="    font-size: 16px; line-height: 150%;"> If the shareholder sells the shares to an Accredited Investor.</li>
                <li class= "faq-answer" style="    font-size: 16px;  line-height: 150%;"> If the shares are sold as part of a registered offering.</li>
                <li class= "faq-answer" style="    font-size: 16px; line-height: 150%;"> If the shares are transferred to a family member or death or divorce.</li>
                <li style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 16px;  line-height: 150%;"> After 1-year (12-months), the shares will be freely tradeable.</li>
                <li style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 16px;  line-height: 150%;"> There is no guarantee your shares will be sold after 1 year.</li>
              </ol>
            </p>

           <p class= "faq-answer">
            (E) Research shows that successful Angel Investors need to made at least 20 investments to have the best chances of success. How can I be successful if I am not a millionaire or able to spend tens of thousands investing?
          </p>
          <p class= "faq-answer paragraph-padding">
            (e) Yes. According to top research, like the Kauffman Foundation’s Study on Returns to Angels in Groups, having at least 20 investments increases your chances of success significantly. Many might think this requires significant amounts of capital set aside to accomplish this and with the traditional model of angel investing it was (individual angel investor in an angel group invests avg. of $25,000 per deal). DreamFunded breaks the mold by allowing our members to invest lower dollar amounts in more companies (as little as $1,000), which enables them to build a more diversified portfolio. Diversification does not guarantee or ensure a profit.
          </p><br>


